45:22.433 --> 45:23.467
Reggie.

45:28.733 --> 45:31.168
It is happening.

45:33.799 --> 45:34.964
Nothing's happening.

45:34.966 --> 45:36.731
- No, no.
- I'm here.

45:36.733 --> 45:39.400
Okay, it's... It's the curse.

45:41.932 --> 45:43.633
It killed my fish.

45:45.432 --> 45:46.364
Honey.

45:46.366 --> 45:48.697
Goldfish die all the time.

45:48.699 --> 45:50.331
You know what?

45:50.333 --> 45:51.864
We'll get another one.

45:51.866 --> 45:52.867
I promise.

45:54.298 --> 45:55.466
I promise.

46:02.433 --> 46:05.464
Hey, you know what?
You know what, baby?

46:05.466 --> 46:08.264
Let's just...
Let's get to sleep.

46:08.266 --> 46:10.530
Let's just go.
Let's just get to sleep.

46:10.532 --> 46:11.533
Okay?

46:12.633 --> 46:14.631
Yeah, there we go.

46:14.633 --> 46:15.634
There we go.

46:16.732 --> 46:18.964
Here we go.

46:18.966 --> 46:21.733
Yeah. There you go, babe.

46:22.565 --> 46:23.566
Yeah.

46:24.699 --> 46:25.700
Okay.

46:27.000 --> 46:30.200
Snug like a bug in a rug.

46:37.632 --> 46:38.666
What?

46:41.599 --> 46:44.663
It's just that it's, um...

46:44.665 --> 46:48.731
It's been a long time
since you hugged me like that.

46:48.733 --> 46:50.763
When you were little,

46:50.765 --> 46:53.630
you used to get scared
and you would make me

46:53.632 --> 46:55.798
stay with you
until you fell asleep.

46:55.800 --> 46:56.800
Mm-hm.

46:57.632 --> 46:59.331
And I would...

46:59.333 --> 47:00.833
I would play in your hair.

47:03.332 --> 47:04.333
Oh.

47:06.800 --> 47:08.200
My beautiful baby.

47:09.332 --> 47:10.833
Now, close your eyes.

47:11.967 --> 47:13.233
Close 'em.

47:13.866 --> 47:14.830
Let's just go to sleep.

47:14.832 --> 47:17.400
It's been a long day
for everybody, right?

47:20.366 --> 47:22.297
The ghost...

47:22.299 --> 47:23.934
The ghosts are gonna get me.

47:25.232 --> 47:27.630
There's no such thing as ghosts.

47:27.632 --> 47:29.299
Ghosts aren't real, baby.

47:30.432 --> 47:34.432
You have nothing
to be afraid of, right?

47:36.366 --> 47:37.367
I guess.

47:40.366 --> 47:41.867
Sweet dreams, my love.

49:20.733 --> 49:22.233
I'm so...

49:22.932 --> 49:24.333
I'm so fucked up.

51:01.833 --> 51:02.834
Uh-huh.

51:03.565 --> 51:04.599
Where were you?

51:07.766 --> 51:08.932
<i>You have to.</i>

51:10.665 --> 51:12.633
<i>It's the only way
to make it stop.</i>

51:14.733 --> 51:15.933
<i>You'll be okay.</i>

51:19.265 --> 51:20.863
<i>You have to kill Elyse.</i>

51:20.865 --> 51:23.533
Okay, I know that you
are going through some things.

51:25.666 --> 51:28.266
But you can't just abandon him
like that, Morgan.

51:30.399 --> 51:31.866
He's 12 years old.

51:33.633 --> 51:35.797
When I was 12, I took care
of myself all the time.

51:42.533 --> 51:43.534
Hey, sweetie.

52:08.899 --> 52:10.200
I hate Halloween.

52:12.233 --> 52:13.866
It was a weird day.

52:17.799 --> 52:21.932
You scared Caleb earlier
with that poem stuff.

52:22.998 --> 52:24.330
I didn't write the damn thing.

52:24.332 --> 52:25.899
I know, but he's a kid, though.

52:27.298 --> 52:28.165
He needs to grow up.

52:32.233 --> 52:33.900
I don't know if I'm ready
for him to.

52:34.666 --> 52:35.699
Look at Morgan.

52:36.998 --> 52:39.331
She's growing up,
and I'm terrified.

52:39.333 --> 52:42.330
What happened to my little girl
who used to...

52:42.332 --> 52:43.798
pick wildflowers with me?

52:45.398 --> 52:47.929
Or... Oh, my god.

52:47.931 --> 52:50.865
Or used to want her toes painted
just like mine?

53:01.398 --> 53:03.296
You should talk to him.

53:03.298 --> 53:04.466
I think he's still up.

53:05.265 --> 53:06.266
I'm beat.

53:08.433 --> 53:09.700
I had a rough day, too.

53:23.733 --> 53:25.399
Son, you awake?

53:27.965 --> 53:29.600
Hey, what are you doing
with the light on?

53:29.965 --> 53:31.167
Reading.

53:34.966 --> 53:36.667
Mom says you're a little scared.

53:39.333 --> 53:40.333
Huh?

53:42.565 --> 53:43.929
It's okay.

53:43.931 --> 53:46.297
It's okay to be a little scared.

53:46.299 --> 53:48.830
What you don't wanna be
is too scared, all right?

53:48.832 --> 53:50.666
So scared
that you can't see straight.

53:52.599 --> 53:55.733
You gotta remember
God's got your back, always.

53:56.799 --> 53:58.564
That's why you are never scared?

53:58.566 --> 54:01.664
Oh, I am, on occasion.

54:01.666 --> 54:04.765
But when I was your age,
I was scared all the time.

54:05.499 --> 54:06.863
Of what?

54:06.865 --> 54:09.896
Um, this guy I knew.

54:09.898 --> 54:12.232
He used to chase me around.

54:14.633 --> 54:15.766
It was terrible.

54:17.865 --> 54:19.233
Take my lunch money.

54:20.498 --> 54:21.730
It was the worst.

54:21.732 --> 54:22.963
But as a kid, it was like

54:22.965 --> 54:24.566
that was the worst thing
in the world.

54:25.233 --> 54:27.363
One day,

54:27.365 --> 54:30.231
I was out by the lake,
I was out by myself.

54:30.233 --> 54:32.332
Setting off a box
of cherry bombs that I had.

54:33.533 --> 54:34.866
He started chasing me,

54:36.566 --> 54:37.797
going after those cherry bombs.

54:37.799 --> 54:39.563
Sent me like right up a tree.

54:39.565 --> 54:42.729
Literally up an old oak tree.

54:42.731 --> 54:46.732
I just sat up there watching him
hover below just like a shark.

54:48.532 --> 54:50.231
He was calling me names,

54:50.233 --> 54:53.634
and saying he was gonna do this
and that to me when I came down.

54:56.864 --> 54:59.798
So, what did you do?

55:01.233 --> 55:02.500
I got scared.

55:04.899 --> 55:05.963
Like really scared.

55:05.965 --> 55:08.798
I mean, so scared
I couldn't see right from wrong.

55:10.931 --> 55:13.796
I just... I mean...

55:13.798 --> 55:15.496
I started lighting
the cherry bombs off

55:15.498 --> 55:18.267
and dropping them
right on his head.

55:20.798 --> 55:22.167
So, what happened?

55:23.298 --> 55:25.929
Something I regret very much.

55:25.931 --> 55:29.832
So I'm trying to tell you, son,
fear, it's a dangerous thing.

55:31.865 --> 55:35.231
But aren't some things
worth being scared of?

55:35.233 --> 55:36.567
Some things, of course.

55:38.764 --> 55:39.932
Like the curse.

55:42.765 --> 55:44.433
Who told you
about the curse?

55:45.499 --> 55:46.797
Kids at school.

55:46.799 --> 55:50.397
They... they say there was this
guy, in the 80s.

55:50.399 --> 55:52.829
He got... He got a Boo.

55:52.831 --> 55:54.662
Yeah, Vietnam vet, right?

55:54.664 --> 55:55.866
Someone Booed him.

55:56.731 --> 55:57.964
He didn't pass it along.

55:57.966 --> 56:00.534
He said it was a prank,
like you did.

56:02.333 --> 56:03.996
That's not a true story, Caleb.

56:03.998 --> 56:05.299
It is true.

56:06.233 --> 56:08.233
Really? What was his name then?

56:09.698 --> 56:10.630
I don't know.

56:10.632 --> 56:13.364
I don't remember.
It was some city name.

56:13.366 --> 56:15.430
Uh, Memphis?

56:15.432 --> 56:16.896
Uh, I, I don't know.

56:16.898 --> 56:17.996
Yeah, Memphis. Uh-huh.

56:17.998 --> 56:19.630
Anyone know this Memphis?

56:19.632 --> 56:21.862
Or just friends of friends
of friends of friends?

56:21.864 --> 56:24.499
Son, that's something they call
"an urban legend."

56:25.932 --> 56:29.733
You believe in talking snakes,
God, angels.

56:32.533 --> 56:33.900
But you don't believe me.

56:34.865 --> 56:36.467
I have seen things, Dad.

56:37.432 --> 56:39.464
All right, you know what?

56:39.466 --> 56:41.267
We'll talk about this blasphemy
in the morning.

58:15.432 --> 58:16.499
Good boy, Torque.

59:25.832 --> 59:27.395
<i>Hey.</i>

59:27.397 --> 59:28.699
<i>Pick up the razor.</i>

59:32.299 --> 59:33.663
Okay.

59:36.631 --> 59:37.699
<i>Okay.</i>

59:38.397 --> 59:39.398
<i>Okay.</i>

59:43.266 --> 59:45.633
- Just do it, you fucking coward.
- <i>Just do it, you fucking coward.</i>

01:00:17.999 --> 01:00:19.763
<i>You stupid fucking bitch.</i>

01:00:19.765 --> 01:00:21.633
<i>Just fucking do it.</i>

01:00:24.432 --> 01:00:27.267
<i>Oh, just fucking...
Just fucking do it.</i>

01:00:27.699 --> 01:00:28.830
<i>Do it!</i>

01:00:42.699 --> 01:00:43.897
Fuck, fuck!

01:03:44.832 --> 01:03:45.900
Oh!

01:04:05.432 --> 01:04:07.833
Oh, James.

01:04:22.598 --> 01:04:24.495
Oh, shoot!

01:04:24.497 --> 01:04:26.730
Honey, you scared me.

01:04:26.732 --> 01:04:27.900
You couldn't sleep either?

01:04:29.265 --> 01:04:30.432
I'm having bad dreams.

01:04:31.231 --> 01:04:32.231
Really?

01:04:34.331 --> 01:04:35.399
Me, too.

01:04:37.931 --> 01:04:39.198
Where is Papa?

01:04:40.332 --> 01:04:41.833
I don't know.
Downstairs, I think.

01:04:44.364 --> 01:04:45.365
So, um...

01:04:46.565 --> 01:04:47.896
Am I gonna get an apology,

01:04:47.898 --> 01:04:49.932
or we're just gonna pretend
like it never happened?

01:04:50.764 --> 01:04:51.832
For what?

01:04:53.631 --> 01:04:56.930
Okay, we're just gonna pretend
like it never happened.

01:04:56.932 --> 01:04:59.499
Girl, you're gonna be the death
of me, literally.

01:05:24.332 --> 01:05:25.432
What was that?

01:05:37.331 --> 01:05:38.399
What was that?

01:06:12.865 --> 01:06:16.466
Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed be Thy name.

01:06:17.232 --> 01:06:18.765
Thy kingdom come.

01:06:20.464 --> 01:06:23.265
Thy will be done on earth
as it is in heaven.

01:06:26.331 --> 01:06:30.630
Give us this day our daily bread
and forgive us our trespasses,

01:06:30.632 --> 01:06:34.597
as we forgive those
who trespassed against us,

01:06:34.599 --> 01:06:39.896
and lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

01:06:39.898 --> 01:06:45.529
For Thine is the kingdom,
and the power, and the glory

01:06:45.531 --> 01:06:49.866
forever and ever. Amen.

01:07:07.232 --> 01:07:08.566
It... It's here.

01:07:09.665 --> 01:07:11.630
- What?
- I told you.

01:07:11.632 --> 01:07:13.362
All we gotta do
is pass it along.

01:07:13.364 --> 01:07:16.765
It'll be fine,
but you didn't believe me.

01:07:17.930 --> 01:07:18.931
None of you did.

01:07:22.898 --> 01:07:23.963
I'm getting
a little tired of having

01:07:23.965 --> 01:07:25.796
this conversation with you.

01:07:25.798 --> 01:07:28.597
I'm not asking you,
I'm telling you,

01:07:28.599 --> 01:07:30.962
go upstairs and go to bed
before you wake everybody up.

01:07:30.964 --> 01:07:32.996
Too late, we're up.

01:07:32.998 --> 01:07:34.732
I'm calling
a fucking family meeting.

01:07:37.231 --> 01:07:39.363
You can't call a family meeting.

01:07:39.365 --> 01:07:41.263
- You don't have the authority...
- Jesus Christ, James!

01:07:41.265 --> 01:07:43.696
It's not parliament.
We need to talk.

01:07:43.698 --> 01:07:44.895
We're not talking about this.

01:07:44.897 --> 01:07:45.996
There is no curse.

01:07:45.998 --> 01:07:47.529
Well, there's something.

01:07:47.531 --> 01:07:48.863
We've all felt something.

01:07:48.865 --> 01:07:50.830
Dad, we've been seeing things.

01:07:50.832 --> 01:07:52.529
Nightmares.

01:07:52.531 --> 01:07:54.529
You left your brother
alone, and he got scared.

01:07:54.531 --> 01:07:56.629
You felt guilty
and had a bad dream.

01:07:56.631 --> 01:07:57.699
It happens!

01:08:00.397 --> 01:08:04.895
We are haunted by our mistakes,
not by ghosts.

01:08:04.897 --> 01:08:06.798
Sometimes, they are the same.

01:08:08.532 --> 01:08:09.565
James?

01:08:11.532 --> 01:08:13.295
What did you see?

01:08:13.297 --> 01:08:14.929
Who says I saw anything?

01:08:14.931 --> 01:08:17.395
Okay, we may not
speak much anymore,

01:08:17.397 --> 01:08:19.563
but I've lived with you
for 20 years.

01:08:19.564 --> 01:08:21.895
I know when something
is upsetting you.

01:08:21.897 --> 01:08:23.529
Really, Elyse?

01:08:23.531 --> 01:08:24.930
What was your first clue?

01:08:25.930 --> 01:08:28.763
Yes, I am upset!

01:08:28.765 --> 01:08:31.229
Because none of you are...
are willing to put your trust

01:08:31.231 --> 01:08:34.328
and your faith into the Heavenly
Father or the earthly one.

01:08:34.331 --> 01:08:35.496
That is me!

01:08:35.497 --> 01:08:37.596
Here we go. The Good Book.

01:08:37.599 --> 01:08:39.328
We're a God-fearing family.

01:08:39.331 --> 01:08:41.930
I lost a child
in this house, James.

01:08:44.964 --> 01:08:46.365
A child!

01:08:50.265 --> 01:08:51.299
I know.

01:08:52.398 --> 01:08:56.495
A child
that we didn't expect, want.

01:08:56.497 --> 01:08:59.796
And until that moment,
I didn't understand.

01:08:59.798 --> 01:09:01.029
You were down here
with the Good Book,

01:09:01.032 --> 01:09:05.299
I was upstairs in the bath,
my, my stomach tied in knots!

01:09:07.663 --> 01:09:09.995
That horrible minute.

01:09:09.997 --> 01:09:13.930
That horrible minute,
it's all I wanted in my life.

01:09:15.665 --> 01:09:17.166
And I wanted to come to you.

01:09:17.997 --> 01:09:21.295
I wanted you to be there for me.

01:09:21.296 --> 01:09:22.696
But you know why I didn't?

01:09:22.698 --> 01:09:24.662
'Cause I knew
what you would say.

01:09:24.665 --> 01:09:27.395
This is God's plan.

01:09:27.398 --> 01:09:29.662
Fuck God if that's His plan!

01:09:29.663 --> 01:09:31.330
I'm not gonna listen to this.

01:09:31.332 --> 01:09:32.395
No. Of course, you're not.

01:09:32.398 --> 01:09:34.665
You don't hear anything
that you don't wanna hear.

01:09:35.997 --> 01:09:37.665
Hey, where do you think
you're going?

01:09:38.731 --> 01:09:40.529
I'm calling Ash and I'm leaving.

01:09:40.532 --> 01:09:42.929
The hell you are. You get
right back here and stay here.

01:09:42.930 --> 01:09:45.733
Why? So you can give us
another sermon?

01:09:48.265 --> 01:09:50.962
She's right. You know,
that's all you ever do.

01:09:50.964 --> 01:09:52.662
You're gonna sit me down again,

01:09:52.663 --> 01:09:54.698
have a conversation
about the coward's way out?

01:09:55.830 --> 01:09:58.764
The only coward that I see here
is you.

